==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|acidité}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|aciditātem}}, accusative singular of {{m|la|aciditās||sourness, acidity}}, from {{m|la|acidus||sour, acid}}. See [[acid]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əˈsɪdɪti/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|acidities}}

# The [[quality]] or state of being acid
# The quality of [[sour]]; [[sourness]]; [[tartness]]; [[sharpness]] to the taste, as in the '''acidity''' of lemon juice.
#: ''Empty stomachs lead to '''acidity''' and leave a sour taste in the mouth.''
# {{lb|en|pathology}} Excessive acid quality, as in [[gastric]] [[secretion|secretions]].

